zzzy
====
zzzy is a simple sleep cycle calculator.


Features
--------
- Tell you when you should go to sleep (your mom)
- Calculate when you should set your alarm clock


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (zzzy is installed into the
/usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install zzzy (if
necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running zzzy
----------------
See the man page for details.


Configuration
-------------
zzzy can be customized by creating a custom config.h and (re)compiling the
source code. This keeps it fast, secure and simple.
